<!-- ===================================================================
     FAQ
     =================================================================== -->
<section id="faq" class="stripe faq">
  <div class="wrap" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1.3fr;gap:60px;align-items:start;">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="h2">Common<br/>questions.</h2>
      <p class="body-lg" style="margin-top:18px;max-width:280px;">Don't see yours? <a href="mailto:hi@attic.it.com">Email us.</a> We answer everything personally.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq__grid reveal" data-delay="1">
      <details>
        <summary>What if I need something immediately?</summary>
        <p>Same- or next-day delivery is included — schedule a return in the app and we'll bring your crate back on the next available window. No rush fees.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do you keep my things safe?</summary>
        <p>Every crate is tagged with a QR code and scanned at every handoff — pickup, intake, shelf placement, and return — so there's a full custody trail. Storage is climate-controlled at 65–72°F. Contents are insured up to $2,000 per crate.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I send crates back if I don't need them anymore?</summary>
        <p>Yes, any time. If a crate is empty at your home, tap "Send it back" in the app and we'll retrieve it at no cost. Your monthly fee for that crate stops at the next billing cycle.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What counts as a "crate"?</summary>
        <p>A heavy-duty 19-gallon milk crate — 27×17×12 inches, with carry handles and a zip-tie-friendly top. We provide them; you don't need to supply your own containers.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How much stuff fits in a crate?</summary>
        <p>Roughly: an entire holiday decor setup, a full season of off-season clothes, or about 20 books and the contents of one bathroom drawer. Most folks order three or four.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do you have a minimum?</summary>
        <p>Nope. Start with one crate, finish with fifty. We don't care — we just want to be useful.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I get started?</summary>
        <p>We're opening Attic to Denver residents in small batches. <a href="#waitlist">Request an invite</a> and we'll send a code as spots open up — usually within a week.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

